parameter.name: Type
parameter.semantics: A string which identify the type of named signal. The possible values must be defined in a dictionary according to the needs (to be described in the GRIM). This field is not specified through Enum value to keep flexibility. Example of value: MagicAction, WhiteCellAction, etc.

parameter.name: Identifier
parameter.semantics: ID of the named signal.According to the Type of signal chosen, this field allows to refer the activate element (Platform ID, Melmil element ID, etc)

parameter.name: Activated
parameter.semantics: State of the named signal. Allows to manage the action carried by the named signal
